column1:
write a python script to use uiautomator2 library to conduct the following steps
1. Open the YouTube app on your device.
2. Tap on your profile picture in the top right corner of the screen.
3. Select "Settings" from the drop-down menu.
4. Scroll down to "Autoplay" and toggle the switch to the right to turn it on.
5. You can also choose whether you want Autoplay to play only on Wi-Fi or on both Wi-Fi and mobile data.
my device name is 38534a424c453098, platformName is Android, platformVersion is 10
column2:
Sorry, as an AI language model, I don't have access to physical devices to test the code. However, here's a sample code that you can modify according to your needs:

```
import uiautomator2 as u2
import time

# Connect to the device
device = u2.connect('38534a424c453098')

# Open YouTube app
device.app_start('com.google.android.youtube')

# Wait for the app to load
time.sleep(5)

# Tap on profile picture
device(resourceId="com.google.android.youtube:id/avatar").click()

# Wait for the drop-down menu to appear
time.sleep(2)

# Select "Settings"
device(text="Settings").click()

# Wait for the settings page to load
time.sleep(2)

# Scroll down to "Autoplay"
device(scrollable=True).scroll.to(text="Autoplay")

# Toggle the switch to the right to turn it on
device(text="Autoplay").right(className="android.widget.Switch").click()

# Choose whether to play only on Wi-Fi or on both Wi-Fi and mobile data
device(text="Autoplay on Wi-Fi only").click()
device(text="Autoplay on Wi-Fi and mobile data").click()

# Close the app
device.app_stop('com.google.android.youtube')
```

Note: Make sure to install the uiautomator2 library before running the script. You can install it using the following command: `pip install uiautomator2`.
